RunGas Group, a Nigerian gas infrastructure company has located its new composite cylinder manufacturing facility in Alaro City, Lagos State’s new city in the Lekki Free Zone. Chief Executive Officer of the firm, Lanre Runsewe, said the company identified the new location as the perfect place for its expansion plans due to the city’s award-winning masterplan and the speed with which infrastructure was being rolled out in the new city. “As RunGas makes progress on our goal of increasing the use of LPG in Nigeria and Africa, such partnerships with business-friendly locations like Alaro City are critical. We will use the five hectares acquired in Alaro City for the production and supply of quality certified, durable, standardised and technologically advanced gas cylinders,” he stated.